communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The 2012 to 2020 Global Measles & Rubella Strategic Plan (http://www.measlesrubellainitiative.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Measles-Rubella-Strategic-Plan.pdf) describes 5 core components of a comprehensive measles and rubella elimination strategy:
- achieve and maintain high levels of population immunity by providing high vaccination coverage with 2 doses of measles and rubella containing vaccines;
- monitor diseases using effective surveillance and evaluate programmatic efforts to ensure progress;
- develop and maintain outbreak preparedness, respond rapidly to outbreaks, and manage cases;
- communicate and engage to build public confidence and demand for immunization;
- perform the research and development needed to support cost-effective operations and improve vaccination and diagnostic tools.

